    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-17T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-17T05:00:00-05:00" n="103"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/14721: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-17T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >February 17, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 17—7:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. Department’s 40, February 15, 8 p.m. Instructions carried out in an interview
                    with the Minister for Foreign Affairs this afternoon.<note n="18"
                        xml:id="d103fn18">For Ambassador Grew’s memorandum of February 17, see <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_830">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 830</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Minister said that the purpose of the occupation of Hainan Island is to
                    strengthen the blockade of the South China coast and to <pb facs="0115" n="111"
                        xml:id="pg_111"/> hasten the suppression of the Chiang Kai Shek “regime”.
                    Arita repeated the former statements of the Japanese Government that Japan has
                    no territorial ambitions in China and added that the occupation “will not go
                    beyond military necessity”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
